ROBERT SLAUGHTER, 470 acs.
(N. L.), Essex Co., in St. Mary’s Par;
on §. side of the Rapidanna River; a
little above the mouth of Hunting Run;
20 Feb. 1719, p. 456. 50 Shill.

HENRY RAINES, WILLIAM HOWARD, & JOHN SUTTON, 464 acs. (N.
L.), K. & Q. Co., in St. Stephen’s Par;
beg. in old line of Prossor & Pannell’s;
to S. side of the N. fork of Otterdam
Swamp; 31 Oct. 1716, p. 299. 50 Shill.

HENRY CLAY, 400 acs. (N. L.),
Henrico Co; on S, side of Swift Cr;
at the mouth of Ephriam Lile’s branch;
on James Eakin’s line; 5 Sept. 1723, p.
241. 40 Shill.

SAME. 400 acs. (N, L.); same location, date, & page. Adj. Col. Cole;
crossing fork of the Indian Camp Br.
40 Shill.
